Task 5.2 – GUI Light Intensity Control

This project uses a Raspberry Pi and PyQt5 to control LED lights through a graphical user interface.
Users can select a room (Living Room, Bathroom, Closet) using radio buttons.

The Living Room LED supports brightness control using a slider with PWM, while the other LEDs can be turned on or off.

Technologies used:

Python (PyQt5 for GUI)
RPi.GPIO and gpiozero (PWMLED)

The system demonstrates basic GUI interaction with hardware and PWM-based light intensity control.
